```python
from fastapi import FastAPI
app = FastAPI()

@app.get('/items/{item_id}')
def read_item(item_id: int, q: str | None = None):
    return {'id': item_id, 'q': q}
```
The `{item_id}` in the path matches the function argument by name; the type hint drives validation and coercion. `q` isn't in the path, so FastAPI treats it as a query parameter (`?q=hello`).

